Name: rdbSysUp
Description: Indicates that the DBWriter system is up and active.

Name: rdbSysDown
Description: Indicates that the DBWriter system is shutting down.

Name: rdbDBConnection
Description: Indicates abnormal condition of database connections.

Name: rdbStatusChange
Description: Indicates the state of the system going from passive to active.

Name: rdbProbeConn
Description: Indicates that the connection with the SS7Probe is lost/gained/paused/resumed.

Name: rdbIMDBConn
Description: Indicates that the connection with the roamer cache server is lost/gained.

Name: rdbTDRConn
Description: Indicates that the connection with the TDR interface is lost/gained.

Name: rdbNoMesgFromProbe
Description: Indicates that no messages are received from Probe for a configurable period.

Name: rdbProbeMsgPoolStatus
Description: Indicates the status of probe message pool.

Name: rdbEventQueue
Description: Indicates the status of event queue.

Name: rdbEODFailure
Description: Indicates that the EOD process has failed.

Name: rdbHeartbeat
Description: Sent periodically to indicate that DBWriter is alive.

Name: rdbAllocatorDeplete
Description: Indicates that an MSU allocator buffer is depleting.

Name: rdbMsgPoolStatus
Description: Indicates the status of message mtp2 pool.

Name: callgwClientConnStatus
Description: Indicates Roamware ISUPGateway Client connection status.

Name: msuProcessingCapacity
Description: Indicates status of number of MTP2 MSU received by DBWriter.

Name: smTimeoutStatus
Description: Indicates status of percentage number statemachines of MTP2 MSU received by DBWriter.

Name: rdbTrapsResync
Description: Indicates the start and end of a trap resync operation.
